gov.usgs.anss.inventory

Class LocationLog

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.inventory.LocationLog

  • public class LocationLog
extends java.lang.Object
    LocationLog.java - Contains transactions about inventory at a site. This includes "pending" for non-tracking items and general Locations. The ideas is that a data list of transactions says a lot about what has happened a a site. If the name of the class does not match the name of the field in the class you may need to modify the rs.getSTring in the constructor. Created on July 8, 2002, 1:23 PM

      • LocationLog

        public LocationLog(int inID,
                   java.lang.String loc,
                   int locid,
                   int main,
                   java.lang.String intype,
                   java.sql.Date d)
        Build a LocationLog from discrete data with no database implication. Some record types like address, contact, geology have only one record in the database. As a new one is posted the old one gets a superceding ID indicating the record that made this one obsolete. The record with a superceding ID of zero is the active record. On multiple transactions the supercedingID has no meaning.
        Parameters:
        inID - DB ID for this record
        loc - Text describing this transaction
        locid - DB ID for this Location
        main - DB ID for a maintenance code (0 if none)
        intype - String matching the Enum on type in table location_log
        d - Completed date - 1970 indicates not completed
